Approach 2: Reverse String (Using StringBuilder)


String s = "madam";

String reverse = new StringBuilder(s).reverse().toString();

if (s.equals(reverse)) {
    System.out.println("Palindrome");
} else {
    System.out.println("Not Palindrome");
}
â± Time Complexity

â¡ï¸ O(n)

ğŸ’¾ Space Complexity

â¡ï¸ O(n)
------------------------------------------------
Approach 3: Without Extra Space (Using Loop + String)
String s = "madam";
String reverse = "";

for (int i = s.length() - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
    reverse += s.charAt(i);
}

System.out.println(s.equals(reverse));
âš ï¸ TC = O(nÂ²) (because of String concatenation)

